    <!-- Setup.Launch.Advanced -->

    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Title">Advanced launch options</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Renderer.Label">Renderer</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Renderer.GameDefault">Game default</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Renderer.Software">Software renderer (llvmpipe)</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Renderer.DirectX12">DirectX 12 (d3d12)</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Renderer.Vulkan">Vulkan (zink)</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Renderer.Warning.Message">Changing this setting will seriously affect game stability and performance. If you do not know what you are doing, do not change this option!&#x0a;Are you sure you want to continue?</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.Renderer.Warning.Confirm">I know what I am doing</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.JvmHead">JVM arguments head</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.JvmHead.Restore">Restore</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.JvmHead.ToolTip">Extra JVM arguments used when launching Minecraft. Do not change unless you are absolutely sure.&#x0a;Supports string replacement tokens from Minecraft instance JSON, e.g. ${library_directory}.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.GameTail">Game arguments tail</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.GameTail.ToolTip">The content in this text box will be directly appended to the end of the launch arguments.&#x0a;For example, entering --demo will start the game in demo mode.&#x0a;String replacement tokens from the Minecraft instance JSON, such as ${library_directory}, are supported.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.PreLaunchCommand">Pre-launch command</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.PreLaunchCommand.ToolTip">Execute a specific command or program before Minecraft launches. The syntax is the same as Windows Command Prompt.&#x0a;&#x0a;The following replacement tokens can be used for relative paths (paths all end with \):&#x0a; · {path}: The folder containing PCL's exe file&#x0a; · {minecraft}: The .minecraft folder&#x0a; · {verpath}: Instance folder (.minecraft\versions\instance_name\)&#x0a; · {verindie}: Same as the instance folder when instance isolation is enabled; otherwise same as the .minecraft folder&#x0a; · {java}: The Java folder used by the game&#x0a;&#x0a;The following replacement tokens are also supported:&#x0a; · {user}: Username&#x0a; · {login}: Login method&#x0a; · {uuid}: Player UUID&#x0a; · {name}: Instance name&#x0a; · {date}, {time}: System time&#x0a; · {version}: Vanilla game version&#x0a;&#x0a;Examples:&#x0a; · &quot;{verpath}test.exe&quot;: Run test.exe in the instance folder&#x0a; · &quot;{java}java.exe&quot; -jar &quot;{verpath}test.jar&quot;: Use Java to run test.jar in the instance folder&#x0a; · notepad &quot;{verindie}options.txt&quot;: Open the instance settings file with Notepad&#x0a;&#x0a;It is recommended to wrap paths in double quotes to avoid launch failures caused by spaces in the path.&#x0a;When the command is executed, the working directory is the current .minecraft folder.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.PreLaunchCommand.Wait">Wait for command completion before continuing launch</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.DisableJlw">Disable Java Launch Wrapper</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.DisableJlw.ToolTip">PCL uses Java Launch Wrapper to fix issues where older Java versions cannot launch from paths containing Chinese characters.&#x0a;If it is blocked by anti-cheat or causes other issues, you can disable it.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.DisableJlw.Arm64Notice">Do not wrap with Java Wrapper when launching the game.&#x0a;Java Wrapper has been forcibly disabled because the system is ARM64 architecture.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.DisableRw">Disable RetroWrapper</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.DisableRw.ToolTip">PCL uses RetroWrapper when launching version 1.5.x and below to improve legacy version gameplay experience and fix compatibility issues.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.GpuPreference">Require Java to use the high-performance GPU</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.GpuPreference.ToolTip">Automatically set Java to use the high-performance GPU in Windows Settings → System → Display → Graphics.&#x0a;If the computer has both integrated and dedicated graphics, this ensures that Minecraft uses the dedicated GPU for rendering, greatly improving performance.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.UseJavaExe">Use java.exe instead of javaw.exe</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.UseJavaExe.ToolTip">If the game window does not appear for a long time, try enabling this option. PCL will use java.exe to run the game, giving the game process standard input/output streams to avoid possible issues when logs are printed.&#x0a;&#x0a;Depending on the behavior of different Java distributions, java.exe may not support features that depend on operating system support, such as HDR colors. Therefore, do not enable this option if everything works normally.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.DisableLwjglUnsafeAgent">Disable LWJGL Unsafe Agent</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.DisableLwjglUnsafeAgent.ToolTip">Minecraft 26.1 uses LWJGL 3.4.1, which uses the FFM API to access native memory on JDK 25+. Due to JDK optimization limitations, this may cause severe performance issues in some cases.&#x0a;PCL uses LWJGL Unsafe Agent to fix this issue and avoid possible performance problems.&#x0a;There is generally no need to disable this option, but if you encounter additional issues, you can try temporarily disabling it for troubleshooting.&#x0a;&#x0a;This feature only takes effect when the LWJGL version is 3.4.1.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.Advanced.MoreInInstanceSetup">You can find more advanced launch options in instance settings.</sys:String>

    <!-- Setup.Launch.Misc -->

    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.Label">Default instance isolation</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.None.ToolTip">All instances use the same profile. Saves, mods, resource packs, and other files are shared.&#x0a;If multiple instances with mods installed are present, this may cause mod conflicts.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.ToolTip">When installing a new instance, the isolation option for the new instance will be automatically set accordingly.&#x0a;To adjust the isolation policy for an existing instance, please go to instance settings.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.ModdedOnly">Isolate instances with mod support</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.ModdedOnly.ToolTip">Isolate instances with mod support like Forge and Fabric to avoid mod conflicts, while other instances like Vanilla are not isolated.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.NonRelease">Isolate non-releases</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.NonRelease.ToolTip">Isolate snapshots, pre-releases, old versions, and April Fools' versions from other instances.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.ModdedAndNonRelease">Isolate instances with mod support and non-releases</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.All">Isolate all instances</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.All.ToolTip">Saves, mods, resource packs, and other files are not shared between instances.&#x0a;Saves will not be shared between Vanilla instances either, so this is generally not recommended.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.InstanceIsolation.DefaultPolicyHint">The default policy only applies to newly installed instances.&#x0a;Existing instances' isolation policy needs to be adjusted in their settings.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.CustomInfo.Label">Custom text</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.CustomInfo.ToolTip">This text will be displayed in the title screen and the F3 debug screen.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.MsAuth.Label">Microsoft login method</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.MsAuth.ToolTip">The Web Account Manager has a simpler Microsoft login flow, while the Device Code Flow allows you to authenticate on any device with a web browser.&#x0a;If you encounter issues with the Web Account Manager, try using the Device Code Flow.&#x0a;If you are temporarily logging in on a public computer, Device Code Flow is recommended.&#x0a;&#x0a;Due to issues with some dependencies, this option is temporarily forced to Device Code Flow.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.MsAuth.WebManager">Web Account Manager (temporarily forced to Device Code Flow)</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.MsAuth.DeviceCode">Device Code Flow</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.IpStack.Label">IP protocol preference</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.IpStack.ToolTip">Set the Minecraft IP protocol preference through JVM arguments.&#x0a;In general, IPv4 preferred is recommended to ensure that the PCL CE lobby works properly.&#x0a;If you need manual IPv6 networking, you can choose another option.&#x0a;&#x0a;IPv4 preferred: -Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true&#x0a;Default: no extra arguments&#x0a;IPv6 preferred: -Djava.net.preferIPv6Stack=true</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Launch.IpStack.Ipv4">IPv4 preferred</sys:String>
