    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Update.Channel.Release">Release</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Update.Channel.Release.ToolTip">A relatively stable version that only receives bug fixes and some built-in resource updates. Suitable for most users.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Update.Channel.Beta">Beta</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Update.Channel.Beta.ToolTip">Potentially unstable beta versions for early feature testing. Suitable for users who want to help test and have some technical ability.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Update.Channel.Dev">Dev</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Update.Channel.Dev.ToolTip">Potentially highly unstable development versions built directly from the latest source code. Suitable for highly technical users.&#x0a;Good internet connectivity may be required to download updates from this channel.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Setup.Update.Channel.Beta.Warning.Message">You are switching the launcher update channel to Beta.&#x0a;Beta versions provide previews of upcoming updates, but may include insufficiently tested features and have reduced stability.&#x0a;&#x0a;After upgrading to Beta, you will need to wait for the next Release version or manually re-download the launcher to switch back to Release.&#x0a;This option is only recommended for users with some basic knowledge and ability. If you are creating a modpack, please use the Release version!</sys:String>
