    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.Renderer.FollowGlobal">Follow global settings</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.JvmArgs.ToolTip">Additional JVM arguments used when launching Minecraft. Do not modify unless you are certain what you are doing.&#x0a;Supports substitution tokens from the Minecraft instance JSON, e.g. ${library_directory}.&#x0a;&#x0a;Leave empty to follow the global setting.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.GameArgs.ToolTip">Content in this text box will be appended directly to the end of the launch arguments.&#x0a;For example, entering --demo will launch the game in demo mode.&#x0a;Supports substitution tokens from the Minecraft instance JSON, e.g. ${library_directory}.&#x0a;&#x0a;Leave empty to follow the global setting.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.Classpath">Additional classpath prefix</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.Classpath.ToolTip">Content will be added as Classpath entries at the head of this instance's launch arguments.&#x0a;Absolute paths are required. Separate multiple entries with English semicolons (;).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.PreLaunchCommand.ToolTip">This does not override the global setting: the global command runs first, then the instance command.&#x0a;&#x0a;Executes a command or program before launching Minecraft, using Windows command prompt syntax.&#x0a;&#x0a;The following substitution tokens can be used for relative paths (paths end with \):&#x0a; · {path}: PCL executable folder&#x0a; · {minecraft}: .minecraft folder&#x0a; · {verpath}: Instance folder (.minecraft\versions\instance-name\)&#x0a; · {verindie}: Version folder when isolation is on, .minecraft folder otherwise&#x0a; · {java}: Java runtime folder&#x0a;&#x0a;Additionally, these tokens are also supported:&#x0a; · {user}: Player name&#x0a; · {login}: Player login method&#x0a; · {uuid}: Player UUID&#x0a; · {name}: Game instance name&#x0a; · {date}, {time}: Current system time&#x0a; · {version}: Game vanilla version&#x0a;&#x0a;Examples:&#x0a; · &quot;{verpath}test.exe&quot; : Run test.exe in the instance folder&#x0a; · &quot;{java}java.exe&quot; -jar &quot;{verpath}test.jar&quot; : Run test.jar from the instance folder with Java&#x0a; · notepad &quot;{verindie}options.txt&quot; : Open the instance settings file with Notepad&#x0a;&#x0a;Always wrap paths in double quotes to avoid failures caused by spaces.&#x0a;The working directory when executing the command is the current .minecraft folder.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.IgnoreJavaCompatibility">Ignore Java compatibility warning</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.IgnoreJavaCompatibility.ToolTip">If a manually selected Java is incompatible with this instance, automatically skip the compatibility warning popup and force the use of the manually selected Java.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.DisableFileVerification">Disable file verification</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.DisableFileVerification.ToolTip">Do not modify Assets at all; do not verify Libraries, third-party login libraries, or the instance main Jar file for modifications.&#x0a;Do not enable this unless you have modified related files.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.UseGlobalProxy">Follow launcher network proxy settings</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instance.Setup.Advanced.UseGlobalProxy.ToolTip">Use the proxy configured in [Settings - Misc - Network - HTTP Proxy] to launch the game.&#x0a;Incorrect global settings will prevent login!</sys:String>
